<br>
My bard is, by far, the most enjoyable character I play.<br>
<br>
For most of my musical career, and until recently, I would always have my weapons out, fighting and twisting as many songs as I could.  It wasn't until I got <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=1448" target="top">Cantana of Soothing</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, which requires a stringed instrument to play, that I first considered standing back, and just playing songs.  But I decided I would best serve my groups to continue meleeing.  It wasn't until I hit lvl46 and I got my fourth percussion DoT song that I started twisting  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=707" target="top">Fufil's Curtailing Chant</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=743" target="top">Tuyen's Chant of Flame</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=3567" target="top">Tuyen's Chant of Disease</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=744" target="top">Tuyen's Chant of Frost</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=2604" target="top">Katta's Song of Sword Dancing</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> while playing a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16396" target="top">Tambourine of Rituals</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Thus doing about 200dmg/tic and increasing group DEX by about 100.  <br>
<br>
I've discovered the great versatility of the bard class by adjusting my role in the group depending on what it's lacking.<br>
I've been in an all melee groups, and have had to play <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=7" target="top">Hymn of Restoration</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on my  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8689" target="top">Combine Mandolin</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Thus playing the role of healer.<br>
If the group I'm in has only one other melee class, I will break out my weapons -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=328" target="top">Symphonic Saber</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and my newly aqcuired <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16448" target="top">Troubadour's Mace</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- and continue to twist songs.  And in the downtime between mobs, I play <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=723" target="top">Cassindra's Chorus of Clarity</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for the casters.<br>
If the group doesn't have a snarer or a slower, I will twist in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=738" target="top">Selo's Consonant Chain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
I've been in FAST pulling groups, in which I spend most of my time mezzing up to 4 adds (the biggest trick there is targeting mobs).<br>
If the group needs more DPS, I will play my DoTs on my <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16396" target="top">Tambourine of Rituals</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Gotta be careful not to take aggro.<br>
<br>
Typically, I twist <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=702" target="top">McVaxius' Berserker Crescendo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=738" target="top">Selo's Consonant Chain</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=1448" target="top">Cantana of Soothing</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=2604" target="top">Katta's Song of Sword Dancing</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=748" target="top">Niv's Melody of Preservation</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
The Cantana requires a stringed instrument (and Niv's Melody benefits from it) so I can't melee.  I used to get into the fight until I realized that my hand2hand skill maxes out at 100, so the small amount of damage I do isn't worth the trouble of manuvering around the mob while continuing to twist.<br>
<br>
Most of the groups I'm in congratulate me on my ability to twist 5 songs at once.  Admittedly, all 5 don't last for very long.  (love my cable modem <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
I've heard tell of bards that swap their weapons for an instrument and back to their weapons DURING a battle, all the while twisting songs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That's a hard working bard.<br>
I've grouped with other bards that play just one song while fighting (usually haste), and don't stop playing it between battles when mana song would be better. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That's a lazy bard.<br>
I'm somewhere in between, closer to a hard working bard.  <br>
<br>
Recently, I entered a group, determined everybody's class, and started twisting my typical 5.  After a few mobs, the group leader booted me out of the group, calling me a leech because I was only playing my songs.<br>
After a couple minutes of shock, I sent the group leader a tell.  I recognized his right as group leader to kick me out, and asked him if he had his song window open (maybe he didn't see that I was playing many songs).  He said that every other bard he'd been grouped with always melee'd, and expected me to do the same.  <br>
<br>
Should a bard ALWAYS melee, ignoring the benefits of their instruments? or should I continue to do as I have been, adjusting my role in the group depending on the group?<br>
<br>
I would like more weapons that double as instruments, but I don't have that much cash, and haven't had the opportunity to get the no drop ones. <br>
<br>
(Gotta learn to get my point across in less than 1,000,000 words <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
-Parodee, 49 Half-Elf Bard<br>
